MMA-31 = OGD-2 Station is in the National Capital Region, city of Quezon near the boundary of Rodriguez, Rizal and Quezon city, barangay Payatas. It is about 25 m. SW of the centerline of the dirt road and about 15 m. above the road surface. Mark is the top of a 5mm. dia. steel bar, 0.60 m. long set flush on top center of a 5 inch. square concrete monument levelled with the ground with inscription OGD-2, 1995. ACCESS: From Rodgriguez Bridge crossing Marikina River in Rodriguez, Rizal, travel W to SW along the road passing Litex Textile mills and solid Aggreagate Co. Inc. crushing plant (dist. 1.20 kms.) Continue travelling towards the uphill and winding dirt rough road going to Quezon city. A small barangay is situated near the hill, then walk SE on a footrail beside the group of houses leading to the small hill. Approx. distance 150 m.

MMA-38 (W-1) Station is in Quezon City, Metro Manila inside the compound of La Mesa Water Treatment Plant. Mark is is a head of copper nail on a 0.25 x 0.25 meters concrete monument protruding 5.0 cms. of adobe ground with inscription "W-1, 1994 , NAMRIA".

MMA-5 = "ENGINEERING 1956" In Diliman, Quezon City inside the Univ. of the Philippines at the center of the deck roof of the kidney-shape elevator penthouse, at the E wing of the Engineering building. Station mark is a regular PC & GS triangulation disk embedded on the concrete roof of the Engineering Bldg. with inscription "ENGINEERING 1956". Latitude is 14° 39' 28.39" and the longitude is 121° 04' 06.187". Reference mark no. 1 is a drill hole with three rays, chiseled around it on the concrete curve of the deck roof, 2.7990 m. N 41° W from the station. Reference mark No. 2 is a similar marker, 3.872 m., N 88° E from the station. Reference mark no. 3 is a similar marker, 2.578 m., S 39° W from the station.

MMA-50 Is in the vicinity of the Manila South Harbor, inside the compound of the Bureau of Coast and Geodetic Survey (BCGS) opposite the Bataan Shipyard and Eng. Corp. (BASECO) compound and the NFA bagging terminal. It is about 100 m. S of the centerline of the road going to the BASECO compound and about 3.6 m. NE of the concrete hollow block perimeter fence of the compound in between two coconut trees. It is almost at the center surface of the square concrete foundation measuring 1.54 m. and 1.36 m., respectively on its side. Mark is a drilled hole 1 cm. in dia. and 2 cm. deep inscribed in a triangle engraved on the surface of the concrete foundation. No inscription. ACCESS: From the Anda circle facing the BIR bldg., travel NW along Bonifacio Drive for about 0.45 km. Then turn right on the road and pass underneath Roxas (Delpan Bridge). Follow the road and heads W towards the BASECO compound. Then stop at the foot of the bridge before entering BASECO compound and walk S for about 100 m. inside the BCGS compound.

Mark is the center of a hexagonal stainless steel bolt drilled to a concrete pavement at the road island along Commonwealth Avenue. ELEVATION : 49.4420 m.

MMA-99 (NF-02) Station is located at the Northwestern sidewalk of Mindanao Ave. It is 6 m NE from the intersection or junction of the sidewalks of Commonwealth and Mindanao Avenues. It is 0.50 m NW from the edge of the road gutter. The mark is also 255 (S 75° W) from a transmission tower located at the eastern side of the intersection. Station mark is the center of a hexagonal stainless steel bolt drilled at the pavement of the sidewalk along Mindanao Avenue.

PIER-8 Station is in the vicinity of Manila Harbor, inside Pier No.8 and about 170 meters behind Solid Shipping lines Building. The station is about 54.76 meters from the north side, 23.12 meters from the west end, and about 22.20 meters from the south side of the pier. Mark is the center of a 5 mm dia. drilled hole centered on a 8" x 8" square concrete monument set flushed on the concrete pier with inscription thus "PIER-8,00,NAMRIA".

PTAG Type of Installation: Roof-based Antenna Model: Leica AR25 REV4 LEIT Receiver Model: Leica GR50 The AGS is located inside NAMRIA compound; antenna is on the roof top of the main building. The station is equipped with auxilliary sensors, i.e. meteorological and tilt sensors.

RZL-4438 From Eulogio Rodriguez Jr. Avenue (C-5 Road) going to Taguig City, turn left to Ortigas Avenue. Travel for about 1.5 km E direction along Ortigas Ave., then turn right and travel 1.6 km SE direction along E. Bank Road, then turn right at Javier Bridge and continue to travel 300 meters SW direction to reach Brgy. May Bunga, Pasig City where the station is established. The station is located at Brgy. May Bunga, Pasig City, along the left top sidewalk F. Legaspi Road going to Rosario, Pasig. Located for about 30 meters E of a police station and between 2 steel post. Mark is the center of a brass rod with cross-cut on top set flush on the center of a 20x20 centimeter cement putty with inscriptions "RZL-4438,2010, DENR IV-A"

TGBM CG-1 ACCESS: TGBM CG-1 is located inside the Philippine Coast Guard Headquarters, Port Area, Manila. it is situated on top of wharf gutter about 0.2m above the wharf floor and 26m Northeast from the base of the tide station. W2A ACCESS: W2A is in Diliman, Quezon City, along University Avenue leading to the University of the Philippines, 16 meters infront of UP marker. STA. MARK: Mark is a top of a Brass rod embedded on a cement putty with inscription "W2A".
